Bat populations in Scotland and across the United Kingdom have declined significantly over the past century.
They are threatened by construction and development work that affects shelter and habitat loss.
Wind turbines and lighting can also pose a danger, as can mosquito nets and certain chemical treatments of building materials, and attacks by pet cats.
Bats aren't actually blind.
